NHL ENTRY DRAFT
June 27, 1998
Dimitri Kalinin
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








Q.  (inaudible)

DIMITRI KALININ:  I am very happy to be a part of this team in the future.  I am very happy to be drafted by Buffalo Sabres.  Very excited.


Q.  (inaudible)

DIMITRI KALININ:  Mostly stay home defenseman, reliable stay home defenseman.


Q.  (inaudible)

DIMITRI KALININ:  They have interviewed me, yeah.  I didn't really give the thought.  To be in the first round is very prestigious and that is what I thought.


Q.  (inaudible)

DIMITRI KALININ:  Ready to go now, but it may take a year or so.  I was very happy, very glad to be on the stage and especially I like the club.  I like the Buffalo Club, so I was very proud to be there.  I like the fact that Alexei Zhitnik, one of the best defensemen is on the team, so I will be happy to play on the line with him, if it is possible.  It looks like it is a very friendly team and I like the style the team plays.  The reason why Vladimir Konstantinov, I see myself after Konstantinov.  I like the way he plays the game.


Q.  (inaudible)

DIMITRI KALININ:  I feel myself very comfortable.  I like the city.  My first impression is very high.


